WIDGETS

Kryon provides 89 widgets.  All widgets have:

    Mandatory properties:
        type        (string, read-only)  Widget type
        rect        (string)             "x y w h"
        visible     (integer)            0 or 1
        enabled     (integer)            0 or 1

    Widget-specific properties:
        text        (string)             Label/caption
        value       (string)             State/value
        placeholder (string)             Hint text

    Events:
        clicked                  Mouse click
        changed                  Value changed
        mouse_enter/leave        Mouse crossing
        focus_gained/lost        Keyboard focus
        key_press/release        Keyboard input

Widget catalog:

Input (24):
    TextInput, PasswordInput, TextArea, SearchInput,
    NumberInput, EmailInput, UrlInput, TelInput,
    Checkbox, RadioButton, Dropdown, MultiSelect,
    ListBox, Switch, Slider, RangeSlider, Rating, Spinbox,
    DateInput, TimeInput, DateTimeInput, MonthInput, WeekInput,
    FileInput

Buttons (8):
    Button, SubmitButton, ResetButton, IconButton,
    FloatingActionButton, DropdownButton, SegmentedControl

Display (11):
    Label, Heading, Paragraph, RichText, Code,
    Image, ProgressBar, ActivityIndicator, Badge,
    Divider, Tooltip

Containers (11):
    Container, Box, Frame, Card, ScrollArea,
    SplitPane, TabContainer, Dialog, Modal,
    ActionSheet, Drawer

Lists (8):
    ListItem, ListTile, ListView, GridView,
    DataTable, TreeView, Chip, Tag

Navigation (8):
    MenuBar, ToolBar, NavBar, NavRail,
    Breadcrumb, Pagination, Stepper, PageView

Menus (4):
    DropdownMenu, ContextMenu, CascadingMenu, PopupMenu

Forms (4):
    Form, FormGroup, ValidationMessage, InputGroup

Windows (4):
    Window, DialogWindow, PageScaffold, Fullscreen

Specialized (8):
    Canvas, Svg, Chart, ColorPicker, SignaturePad,
    Resizable, Calendar, TableView

Layout system:

    Container widgets support:
        layout          "row", "column", "grid", "absolute"
        gap             integer       pixels between children
        padding         integer       pixels around edges
        align           "start", "center", "end", "stretch"
        justify         "start", "center", "end", "space-between"

    Row layout:
        Children arranged horizontally
        Height determined by tallest child
        Widths expand to fill

    Column layout:
        Children arranged vertically
        Width determined by widest child
        Heights expand to fill
